---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About – Backporting.ai" description="About the maintainer and curator of Backporting.ai">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">About the Author</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600">Meet the person behind Backporting.ai</p>
    </div>

    <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-sm">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-64 h-64 bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-100/50 to-indigo-100/50 blur-3xl -z-0"></div>
      
      <div class="relative z-10">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 sm:gap-8 items-start mb-8">
          <!-- Author Avatar/Icon -->
          <div class="flex-shrink-0">
            <img 
              src="/avatar.jpg" 
              alt="Nikita Ivanov" 
              class="w-24 h-24 sm:w-32 sm:h-32 rounded-full object-cover shadow-lg ring-2 ring-slate-200"
            />
          </div>
          
          <!-- Author Header -->
          <div class="flex-1">
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-2 sm:gap-3 mb-4">
              <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold text-slate-900">
                Nikita Ivanov
              </h2>
              <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-sky-100 text-sky-700 text-xs font-medium self-start">
                <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.403 12.652a3 3 0 000-5.304 3 3 0 00-3.75-3.751 3 3 0 00-5.305 0 3 3 0 00-3.751 3.75 3 3 0 000 5.305 3 3 0 003.75 3.751 3 3 0 005.305 0 3 3 0 003.751-3.75zm-2.546-4.46a.75.75 0 00-1.214-.883l-3.483 4.79-1.88-1.88a.75.75 0 10-1.06 1.061l2.5 2.5a.75.75 0 001.137-.089l4-5.5z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                Maintainer & Curator
              </span>
            </div>
            
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              <a 
                href="https://github.com/Roo4L" 
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-slate-100 hover:bg-slate-200 text-slate-700 text-sm font-medium transition-colors"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.484 2 12.017c0 4.425 2.865 8.18 6.839 9.504.5.092.682-.217.682-.483 0-.237-.008-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.605-3.369-1.343-3.369-1.343-.454-1.158-1.11-1.466-1.11-1.466-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.032 1.531 1.032.892 1.53 2.341 1.088 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.113-4.555-4.951 0-1.093.39-1.988 1.029-2.688-.103-.253-.446-1.272.098-2.65 0 0 .84-.27 2.75 1.026A9.564 9.564 0 0112 6.844c.85.004 1.705.115 2.504.337 1.909-1.296 2.747-1.027 2.747-1.027.546 1.379.202 2.398.1 2.651.64.7 1.028 1.595 1.028 2.688 0 3.848-2.339 4.695-4.566 4.943.359.309.678.92.678 1.855 0 1.338-.012 2.419-.012 2.747 0 .268.18.58.688.482A10.019 10.019 0 0022 12.017C22 6.484 17.522 2 12 2z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                View on GitHub
              </a>
              <a 
                href="mailto:hello@backporting.ai" 
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-sky-100 hover:bg-sky-200 text-sky-700 text-sm font-medium transition-colors"
              >
                <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 8l7.89 5.26a2 2 0 002.22 0L21 8M5 19h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z" />
                </svg>
                Get in Touch
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="prose prose-slate prose-lg max-w-none">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4">Welcome to Backporting.ai</h3>
          
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            My name is Nikita. I am a Backporting Automation Researcher from Tuxcare. For the two years
            of my life I have been backporting patches for various OSS projects, from vim to  glibc and openssl.
            For the next two - helping Tuxcare to automate this process and scale its product base. Per my job
            I have to keep up with latest news in the patch backporting field and broader Automated Vulnerability Repair (AVR) topic.
            This website is my contribution to the community of all people involved.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Every article, digest, and resource you find here is carefully curated to provide value 
            to the community. Whether you're conducting research, implementing backporting solutions, 
            or simply staying informed about the latest developments—this platform is for you.
          </p>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4">Mission</h3>
          
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            The goal of Backporting.ai is to assemble in one place all information related to patch 
            backporting automation. This includes academic research papers, blog posts, open-source 
            projects, company releases, and updates from the community.
          </p>

          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            By providing curated content and periodic digests, this platform aims to:
          </p>

          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-700 space-y-2 mb-4">
            <li>Keep interested people updated on the most important developments in the field</li>
            <li>Provide researchers a platform for sharing their work</li>
            <li>Connect people doing research and give them opportunities to collaborate, review, and discuss</li>
            <li>Make patch backporting automation more accessible and understood</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-4">Get Involved</h3>
          
          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            If you have research, tools, or insights related to patch backporting automation that you'd 
            like to share, please reach out. This platform thrives on community contributions and 
            collaboration.
          </p>

          <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
            You can contact me via <a href="mailto:hello@backporting.ai" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 font-medium">email</a> 
            or contribute directly on <a href="https://github.com/Roo4L/backporting_ai" class="text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 font-medium" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

